1
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:31,600
Mr Victor Albert is the greatest
operatic composer living today.

2
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:34,640
- You make it clear, signor.
- Don't interrupt.

3
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:39,280
As his personal manager, l must be sure
that everything is ready for his arrival.

4
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:41,320
l will make doubly sure.

5
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:45,560
Enrico? Make sure that everyone
has their costumes

6
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:48,880
and prepare them
for inspection immediately.

7
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:51,280
Nothing must go wrong with our plans.

8
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:53,760
Not only have l rented every room here

9
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:57,520
but l've provided
the most beautiful Tyrolean costumes.

10
00:01:57,560 --> 00:02:01,280
Every employee with whom
Mr Victor Albert comes into contact

11
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:03,520
must create the proper atmosphere.

12
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:06,560
Mr Albert's Tyrolean opera
is to be his masterpiece.

13
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:08,640
- Do l make myself clear?
- Si, signor.

14
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:13,520
We will do all we possibly can
to make the maestro comfortable.

15
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:17,280
Excuse me, signor.
Mr Albert's wife, she's coming too?

16
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:20,440
No! Absolutely no.
The maestro is to be alone.

17
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:36,840
- How far are we from Pontresina?
- About 50km, monsieur.

18
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:41,080
- And to the top of the mountain?
- Two more kilometres to the hotel.

19
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:43,760
(Practising scales)

20
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,640
Everybody!

21
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:52,600
# La la la la la la la la la

22
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:55,640
# Laaaaaa #

23
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:01,200
- You like it?
- That's fine, Luigi.

24
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,240
Now, let me see your costume.

25
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,880
- Me?
- Certainly.

26
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,920
Why? l am the manager.

27
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:10,480
l said that everyone must wear a costume.

28
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:12,520
Even me.

29
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,360
# To the... (Voice cracks) #

30
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,440
- (Giggling)
- Quiet!

31
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,920
Er...monsieur.

32
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,960
Yes, what is it, Joseph?

33
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,720
You've, er, forgotten your trousers.

34
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:34,040
These are trousers. Tyrolean trousers!

35
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:36,080
- My hat, Joseph.
- Yes, monsieur.

36
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,440
And remember, Joseph...

37
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:43,680
no one is to know that l am here.

38
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,480
No one.

39
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,440
- Especially my wife.
- Yes, monsieur.

